  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Grazing Lands, Livestock and Climate Resilient Mitigation in the Kafue Basin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Zambia the different components of our livestock project are coming together with a more solid involvement from the local leadership. An excursion spurred the adoption of holistic grassland management, following the concept of high density planned rotation on 60,700 hectares. 300 cattle farmers were additionally trained in good practices of controlled burning, intercropping and manure compositing. The use of our cattle grading mobile application is becoming functional, providing both a tool for making better business deals and serving as an awareness building tool for cattle farmers. The combination of 23 village saving and loan associations (VSLA&#x2019;s) used by 435 famers, with training of 61 youth on entrepreneurship and improved leather treatment in 4 village factories with 52 trainees, provides a powerful emerging combination of downstream value creation for the rural communities. The impact is clear with improved yields for maize (35%) and better calving rates (85%) leading to a higher income (103,000 euros collectively) and increased participation of youth and women (nearing 50%). A business model is emerging and even with Covid-19, the targets were surpassed in 2020, while ramping up the services and numbers of beneficiaries will be the major challenge for 2021.</narrative>
  </description>
